<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="passive-adj">passive <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pæsɪv/    美 /'pæsɪv/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>消极的；被动的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A bad mood is a passive reflection of outer factors in one’s daily life.
坏心情是对日常生活中外在因素的消极反应。</p><footer>2009 江西书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>passive smoking</strong>
被动吸烟；吸二手烟</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>被动的</strong></h4>
<p>反 active </p>
<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>passively /'pæsɪvli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Listening is thus an active, not a <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (被动的), behavior consisting of hearing, understanding and remembering.  （2015 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. passive  </p></div>